            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">Spring 2026:</span> <strong>Attorney decision: refi-bridge to buy the protected condo BEFORE the support-property sale clears, or wait?</strong> Buying first requires a primary house refi as a short-lived bridge (extra closing costs ~$5–10k) but avoids the summer market spike on the protected condo. Buying after avoids the refi but exposes the household to seasonal price movement on the target condo.</li>
