            {{!-- Optimizer starts at LTC disbursement --}}
            {{#if scenario.optimizer_enabled}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px; color: #27ae60;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{scenario.ltc_trigger_year}}:</span> <strong>Optimized cash withdrawal strategy activates</strong> — automatically selects lowest yearly opportunity-cost, IRA vs. LTC, prioritizing solvency</li>
            {{/if}}

            {{!-- Nursing intensifies → start looking for MC facility --}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;" id="intensifyYearLabel"></span> As nursing needs intensify, begin searching for a memory care facility that <strong>guarantees (in writing) a Medicaid bed after 2–3 years of private pay</strong></li>

            {{!-- Memory care --}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.memory_care_year 2032}}:</span> primary household enters memory care facility — private-pay window begins</li>

            {{!-- Roommate --}}
            {{#if scenario.roommate_enabled}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px; color: #66ccff;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.memory_care_year 2032}}:</span> <strong>support household takes roommate(s)</strong> — <span style="color: #66ccff;">${{formatNumber (or scenario.roommate_monthly 1100)}}/mo</span> additional <strong>protection-trust income</strong> to help cover house expenses</li>
            {{/if}}

            {{!-- Medicaid activation --}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{add (or scenario.memory_care_year 2032) 3}}:</span> <strong>Pre-Medicaid IRA liquidation</strong> — all remaining IRA &amp; annuities liquidated into the SNT BEFORE Medicaid application (~$159k tax withholding), protecting these funds from Medicaid seizure so they can maintain the primary house and cover trust obligations</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{add (or scenario.memory_care_year 2032) 3}}:</span> Pay off remaining SNT condo mortgage (if any), then file Medicaid application; lookback period (5 years from 2026 transfers) cleared in 2031</li>

            {{!-- At client household's death --}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}} (primary household's death):</span> <strong>Stepped-up basis</strong> on primary house and any remaining trust assets via §2041 LPOA → §1014 — eliminates accumulated capital gains</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}}:</span> Sell primary house at stepped-up basis (~$1.6M projected proceeds, $0 capital gains)</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}}:</span> Pay projected estate tax (~$118k on a ~$2.1M estate)</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}}:</span> <strong>Repay the support household's documented $404k equity claim</strong> from house sale proceeds (legally enforceable per Summer 2026 acknowledgment)</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• <span style="color:#888;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}}:</span> Distribute remaining protection-trust assets in equal thirds to the fiduciary, dependent household, and support household — the dependent household's share is offset by trust inheritance to maintain even allocation</li>

            {{!-- Planning horizon --}}
            <li style="margin-bottom: 8px;">• Planning horizon through <span style="color: #66ccff;">{{or scenario.year_of_passing 2040}}</span> (primary household age {{add 70 (subtract (or scenario.year_of_passing 2040) 2026)}}) — <span id="survivalPctDecision"></span></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

